<content start="9" end="10">
<component><class>org.concord.modeler.PageTextBox</class>
<width>750.0</width>
<height>120.0</height>
<title>&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body face=&quot;verdana&quot;&gt;
    Some materials, such as silicon crystals, do not conduct electricity well 
    at very low temperature--the electrons are tightly bound to atoms and 
    behave like those in insulators. But when temperature increases, some 
    electrons become loose and can &amp;quot;hop&amp;quot; from one atom to another, resulting 
    in conductivity. Because the electrical conductivity of these materials 
    lies between insulators and conductors, they are called semiconductors.
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</title>
<opaque>false</opaque>
</component></content>

