  &lt;body face=&quot;verdana&quot;&gt;
    The following simulation shows how electrons move in a silicon crystal at 
    different temperatures. The gray shapes show the covalent bonds between 
    silicon atoms. The dashed circles show the electron positions in the 
    bonds. When they are not occupied by an electron, they represent a hole.

    &lt;p&gt;
      &lt;b&gt;Instructions:&lt;/b&gt; 1) Click the &amp;quot;Run&amp;quot; button and observe what happens. 
